  "2026-06-14T19:20:49.349Z",lane-b-subagent-20260614,"Lane B coverage implementation evidence:\n- Refactored Lane-B unit tests to import package/runtime TypeScript sources directly (beads, todos, search-advanced, extension entrypoints, command-kit) and added deterministic cache-busting for dynamic imports.\n- Added new focused suites: tests/unit/lane-b-package-runtime-coverage.spec.ts and tests/unit/lane-b-scripts-coverage.spec.ts to cover package runtime wrappers/loaders/indexes plus docs/examples and plugin scripts.\n\nVerification command outcomes:\n1) PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/lane-b-package-runtime-coverage.spec.ts tests/unit/lane-b-scripts-coverage.spec.ts\n   -> PASS (2 files, 14 tests).\n2) PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/builtin-extension-entrypoints.spec.ts tests/unit/beads-command.spec.ts tests/unit/todos-extension.spec.ts tests/unit/search-advanced-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/extension-command.spec.ts tests/unit/lane-b-package-runtime-coverage.spec.ts tests/unit/lane-b-scripts-coverage.spec.ts\n   -> PASS (7 files, 155 tests).\n3) PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage -- tests/unit/builtin-extension-entrypoints.spec.ts tests/unit/beads-command.spec.ts tests/unit/todos-extension.spec.ts tests/unit/search-advanced-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/extension-command.spec.ts tests/unit/lane-b-package-runtime-coverage.spec.ts tests/unit/lane-b-scripts-coverage.spec.ts --coverage.thresholds.lines=0 --coverage.thresholds.functions=0 --coverage.thresholds.branches=0 --coverage.thresholds.statements=0\n   -> PASS (7 files, 155 tests), coverage report generated.\n\nMeasured coverage movement for strict Lane-B families (from coverage/coverage-summary.json aggregate):\n- packages/**/*.ts: lines 87.42% -> 94.22%, statements 87.59% -> 94.21%, functions 83.78% -> 92.27%, branches 79.69% -> 87.08%.\n- plugins/**/*.mjs: lines 46.91% -> 88.89%, statements 45.65% -> 88.04%, functions 55.56% -> 100.00%, branches 34.00% -> 70.00%.\n- docs/examples/**/*.js|mjs|ts: lines 90.83% -> 100.00%, statements 91.07% -> 100.00%, functions 100.00% -> 100.00%, branches 55.32% -> 69.15%.\n\nRemaining non-100 files are concentrated in branch-heavy runtime/loader paths (e.g. calendar runtime, beads/todos runtime-loaders, guide-shell runtime, plugin mcp wrapper spawn/repo resolution branches).}"
  "2026-06-14T19:52:31.912Z",lane-b-wave2-subagent-20260614,"Wave2 lane-B coverage evidence:\n- Added focused suites: tests/unit/lane-b/package-runtime-wave2.spec.ts, tests/unit/lane-b/docs-examples-wave2.spec.ts, tests/unit/lane-b/plugin-scripts-wave2.spec.ts.\n- Command: PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/lane-b/package-runtime-wave2.spec.ts tests/unit/lane-b/docs-examples-wave2.spec.ts tests/unit/lane-b/plugin-scripts-wave2.spec.ts\n  Result: PASS (3 files, 11 tests).\n- Command: PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage -- tests/unit/lane-b/package-runtime-wave2.spec.ts tests/unit/lane-b/docs-examples-wave2.spec.ts tests/unit/lane-b/plugin-scripts-wave2.spec.ts --coverage.thresholds.lines=0 --coverage.thresholds.functions=0 --coverage.thresholds.branches=0 --coverage.thresholds.statements=0\n  Result: PASS; coverage-summary regenerated.\n- Family movement (before -> after): docs/examples lines 0.00 -> 96.33, branches 0.00 -> 65.96; plugins lines 0.00 -> 90.12, branches 0.00 -> 68.00; package runtime wrappers lines 0.00 -> 93.24, branches 0.00 -> 80.36.\n- Key target files (lines pct): calendar runtime 0.00 -> 88.88; governance runtime 0.00 -> 96.87; guide-shell runtime 0.00 -> 92.56; linked-test-adapters runtime 0.00 -> 96.87; templates runtime 0.00 -> 100.00; claude session-start 0.00 -> 100.00; claude pm-mcp-server 0.00 -> 89.28; codex pm-mcp-server 0.00 -> 82.14; sdk app embedding example 0.00 -> 100.00; sdk contract consumer example 0.00 -> 100.00; starter extension example 0.00 -> 94.02."
  "2026-06-14T19:59:49.224Z",lane-b-wave2-subagent-20260614,"Wave-2 lane-B coverage evidence:\n- Updated existing lane-b suites in tests/unit/lane-b to add deterministic branch coverage for docs examples, plugin session-start/MCP wrappers, and targeted package runtimes.\n- Focused verification command 1: PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/lane-b/package-runtime-wave2.spec.ts tests/unit/lane-b/plugin-scripts-wave2.spec.ts tests/unit/lane-b/docs-examples-wave2.spec.ts\n  Result: PASS (3 files, 12 tests).\n- Focused verification command 2: PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage -- tests/unit/lane-b/package-runtime-wave2.spec.ts tests/unit/lane-b/plugin-scripts-wave2.spec.ts tests/unit/lane-b/docs-examples-wave2.spec.ts --coverage.thresholds.lines=0 --coverage.thresholds.functions=0 --coverage.thresholds.branches=0 --coverage.thresholds.statements=0\n  Result: PASS (3 files, 12 tests) with coverage report generated.\n- Measured movement (baseline probe before edits -> final probe after edits):\n  * docs/examples target set avg lines 98.50% -> 100.00%; avg branches 74.66% -> 85.53%.\n  * plugin target set avg lines 90.47% -> 100.00%; avg branches 69.69% -> 89.17%.\n  * targeted package runtime set avg lines 95.04% -> 98.92%; avg branches 84.07% -> 88.73%.\n- Key per-file gains:\n  * packages/pm-calendar/extensions/calendar/runtime.ts lines 88.88% -> 100.00%.\n  * packages/pm-governance-audit/extensions/governance-audit/runtime.ts lines 96.87% -> 100.00%.\n  * packages/pm-linked-test-adapters/extensions/linked-test-adapters/runtime.ts lines 96.87% -> 100.00%.\n  * plugins/pm-claude/scripts/pm-mcp-server.mjs lines 89.28% -> 100.00%.\n  * plugins/pm-codex/scripts/pm-mcp-server.mjs lines 82.14% -> 100.00%.\n  * docs/examples/starter-extension/index.js lines 94.02% -> 100.00%.\n- Remaining notable gap in this focused sweep: packages/pm-guide-shell/extensions/guide-shell/runtime.ts remains below full line coverage (94.59%), with uncov lines concentrated in runtime-completion edge paths."
  "2026-06-15T03:26:13.375Z",claude-code-agent,"Lane B wave3 (opus orchestration, 2026-06-15): sub-agent lane-b-agent-20260614-opus ran ~40min (116 tool calls), cut off by session-limit pre-documentation. Landed: new tests/unit/lane-b/runtime-loaders-wave3.spec.ts (beads/todos dynamic ESM runtime-loader success+failure branches) + extended beads-command, todos-extension, builtin-extension-entrypoints, search-advanced-runtime, extension-command specs. Orchestrator fixed one cut-off-left broken assertion in builtin-extension-entrypoints.spec.ts:494 (calendar renderer returns null only for non-calendar result, not by command name)."
  "2026-06-15T14:58:15.030Z",coverage-packages-agent,"Packages + docs/examples module-mirrored coverage restoration (branch test/all-source-100pct-coverage-gate).\n\nSpec files created (ADR pm-kjmx module-mirrored convention, CLEAN titles, no lane/wave vocabulary):\n- tests/unit/docs-examples/policy-restricted-extension.spec.ts (ported from docs-examples-wave2.spec.ts policy block) -> docs/examples/policy-restricted-extension/index.js\n- tests/unit/docs-examples/starter-extension.spec.ts (ported from docs-examples-wave2.spec.ts starter block; complements existing tests/unit/starter-extension-example.spec.ts which only asserts the migration source string, no duplicated assertions) -> docs/examples/starter-extension/index.js\n- tests/unit/docs-examples/sdk-app-embedding.spec.ts (ported from docs-examples-wave2.spec.ts) -> docs/examples/sdk-app-embedding/run-embedded-pm.mjs\n- tests/unit/docs-examples/sdk-contract-consumer.spec.ts (ported from docs-examples-wave2.spec.ts) -> docs/examples/sdk-contract-consumer/inspect-contracts.mjs\n- tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts (ported from runtime-loaders-wave3.spec.ts; parametrized describe.each over both pm-beads and pm-todos) -> packages/pm-beads/extensions/beads/runtime-loader.ts + packages/pm-todos/extensions/todos/runtime-loader.ts\n- tests/unit/packages/todos-runtime-errors.spec.ts (ported from todos-export-errors-wave4.spec.ts) -> packages/pm-todos/extensions/todos/runtime.ts\n- tests/unit/packages/linked-test-adapters-runtime.spec.ts (extracted ONLY the linked-test-adapters block from package-runtime-wave2.spec.ts, with self-contained header helpers) -> packages/pm-linked-test-adapters/extensions/linked-test-adapters/runtime.ts\n- tests/unit/packages/templates-runtime.spec.ts (extracted ONLY the templates block from package-runtime-wave2.spec.ts) -> packages/pm-templates/extensions/templates/runtime.ts\n\nDEDUP decisions: package-runtime-wave2.spec.ts ALSO contained calendar / governance-audit / guide-shell blocks; these were NOT ported because tests/unit/packages/{calendar-runtime,governance-audit-runtime,guide-shell-runtime,search-advanced}.spec.ts already fully cover those runtimes. Only linked-test-adapters and templates were extracted. No assertions duplicated across files.\n\nNOTE on target paths: the policy/starter examples have NO .ts source on disk - only index.js (vitest.config coverage include is docs/examples/**/*.js). Specs correctly import the compiled .js.\n\nPer-module coverage AFTER (each verified 100/100/100/100 statements/branches/functions/lines):\n- docs/examples/policy-restricted-extension/index.js 100/100/100/100\n- docs/examples/starter-extension/index.js 100/100/100/100\n- docs/examples/sdk-app-embedding/run-embedded-pm.mjs 100/100/100/100\n- docs/examples/sdk-contract-consumer/inspect-contracts.mjs 100/100/100/100\n- packages/pm-beads/extensions/beads/runtime-loader.ts 100/100/100/100\n- packages/pm-todos/extensions/todos/runtime-loader.ts 100/100/100/100\n- packages/pm-todos/extensions/todos/runtime.ts 100/100/100/100\n- packages/pm-linked-test-adapters/extensions/linked-test-adapters/runtime.ts 100/100/100/100\n- packages/pm-templates/extensions/templates/runtime.ts 100/100/100/100\nBEFORE: each was <100% on this branch because their lane coverage was removed (lane-b/*wave*.spec.ts deleted). Faithful porting + dedup restored 100%.\n\nVerification commands (PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1, no pnpm build):\n1) Combined run of the .ts targets together with all their other covering specs (beads-command, todos-extension, builtin-extension-entrypoints, templates-command, package-manifest, starter-extension-example), coverage.include scoped to the 7 .ts/.mjs targets:\n   18 test files / 138 tests PASS; aggregate 100% Stmts 341/341, Branch 275/275, Funcs 43/43, Lines 340/340; per-file json-summary all OK at 100.\n2) Examples .js run (tests/unit/docs-examples/ + starter-extension-example.spec.ts), coverage.include scoped to the two index.js files: both OK 100/100/100/100.\nAll 40 tests in tests/unit/docs-examples/ + tests/unit/packages/ pass deterministically. No .only, no skips, no source changes (no dead-branch refactors needed). Clean (no lane/wave) describe titles confirmed via grep."
